tedomari is a C++/SDL Sakusen client

tedomari is free software, distributed under the terms of the GNU General
Public License, version 2.  For more information, see the file COPYING.

To compile, requires either both libsakusen and libsakusen-comms checked out in
appropriately named parallel directories or else for things to be laid out as
in the repository.

Additionally, compilation requires the following libraries (their corresponding
Debian package names are also given):

readline  libreadline5-dev
unicode   libunicode-dev

